{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2026-1130","published":"2026-01-16T11:59:52Z","modified":"2026-01-16T12:30:16.434028Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-67725"],"summary":"python-tornado security update","details":"Tornado is an open source version of the scalable, non-blocking web server and tools.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nTornado is a Python web framework and asynchronous networking library. In versions 6.5.2 and below, a single maliciously crafted HTTP request can block the server&apos;s event loop for an extended period, caused by the HTTPHeaders.add method. The function accumulates values using string concatenation when the same header name is repeated, causing a Denial of Service (DoS).  Due to Python string immutability, each concatenation copies the entire string, resulting in O(nÂ²) time complexity. The severity can vary from high if max_header_size has been increased from its default, to low if it has its default value of 64KB. This issue is fixed in version 6.5.3.(CVE-2025-67725)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"python-tornado","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/python-tornado&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"6.5-2.oe2403sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["python-tornado-debuginfo-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","python-tornado-debugsource-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","python-tornado-help-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","python3-tornado-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["python-tornado-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["python-tornado-debuginfo-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","python-tornado-debugsource-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","python-tornado-help-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","python3-tornado-6.5-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2026-1130.json"}},{"package":{"name":"python-tornado","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/python-tornado&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS